>record scratch
>you're probably wondering how I got in this situation

It all started in high school a little less than a decade ago. Junior year I found myself intermingling with a group of other socially awkward teenagers. There was Paul, who was the "leader" of the group, Lacey, the token chubby girl who thought she was hot shit, John, who is the most important in this situation, and me, Tabletop-Anon.

Me and John got along the best out of the group, seeing as we shared many of the same classes and interests. He'd spend most of his time either doing the class work or drawing. What did he draw? For the longest time I had no clue since he was really protective of it and didn't let anyone see it besides himself.

Come the end of the year and during passing time, where you go from class to class, someone that had always made fun of him tried to take the binder he kept all the pictures in. Now, John wasn't a slouch. He had always talked about the times he got trained by a parent's friend that was the golden gloves champion of [insert state here] for a while, so when the person tried to take the binder they ended up getting sent to the nurses office.

A piece of paper had slid out of his binder amidst the spectacle of seeing a nerdy, somewhat bulky dude drop a guy nearly twice his size. I slid it into my pocket and waited until I got home to look at it.

It simply said e621. Now, this was in 2008, so the site didn't have nearly as much traction as it does now. I searched it up and got thrown into the rabbit hole. Now I'm stuck here with you lot, a group of funny, disfunctional asshats and I wouldn't want it any other way.

-Tabletop-Anon

I pretty much used some Gundam-related stuff (Who would have guessed) as inspiration for the Aegis units.
The "one-off" units were pretty much inspired by the Jesta (Meaning pretty much the base is the same, but the details are a bit different for each unit)

>https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/08/FD-03_Gustav_Karl_UC_Front.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20160831104250

>https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8e/RX-78AL_Gundam_Atlas.png/revision/latest?cb=20150303121246
